trans-unit.source:
Immediate: The prefetching of pages occurs instantly when a user loads a page.
Eager: Fetching starts once the current page transfer is complete and the browser is idle.
Moderate: Fetching starts only when the user interacts with the page, such as scrolling or clicking.
Conservative: Fetching occurs when the user clicks a link or performs another action indicating they will soon need the resource.
Preload this page with the Speculation-API settings
This page will not be preloaded

Prefetching hints to the browser that a resource might be needed in the future.
Prerendering involves rendering a page in the background so it can be quickly displayed when the user navigates to it.
